00:00:24.730 --> 00:00:26.938
to see we're going to get
the same expressions, which

00:00:26.938 --> 00:00:28.910
will show us that
Stokes' theorem is true,

00:00:28.910 --> 00:00:31.487
at least for this
special class of surfaces

00:00:31.487 --> 00:00:32.820
that we are studying right here.

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:34.510
But they're pretty general.

00:00:34.510 --> 00:00:36.894
