Well, we've already figured
out what our curl of F

00:01:02.390 --> 00:01:04.060
is here two videos ago.

00:01:04.060 --> 00:01:06.250
And we've almost
figured out what ds is.

00:01:06.250 --> 00:01:09.660
ds is the cross product of
these two vectors times dA.

00:01:09.660 --> 00:01:11.290
The cross product
of these two vectors

00:01:11.290 --> 00:01:12.780
is this right over here.

00:01:12.780 --> 00:01:16.330
So we could just
write that ds is

00:01:16.330 --> 00:01:19.570
going to be equal to
this thing times dA.

00:01:19.570 --> 00:01:21.470
This is the cross
product of the partial

00:01:21.470 --> 00:01:24.490
of r with respect to x and the
partial of r with respect to y.

00:01:24.490 --> 00:01:27.780
And then we have to multiply
that times dA right over there.

00:01:27.780 --> 00:01:29.995
So this expression is
just going to be the dot

00:01:29.995 --> 00:01:36.140
product of the curl of F, which
is this stuff up here dotted

00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:37.720
with this stuff down here.

00:01:37.720 --> 00:01:38.530
And essentially, we're
going to take the dot

00:01:38.530 --> 00:01:40.620
product of this
vector and that vector

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:42.840
and then multiply it times
this-- we can actually

00:01:42.840 --> 00:01:44.840
consider this to
be a scalar value.

00:01:44.840 --> 00:01:45.870
So let's do that.

00:01:45.870 --> 00:01:47.940
So this is going to
be equal to-- and

00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.090
when we do this, all
of these we are now

00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:53.490
going to start operating in
the domain of our parameters.

00:01:53.490 --> 00:01:55.850
So it's going to turn
from a surface integral

00:01:55.850 --> 00:01:58.280
into a double integral
over that domain,

00:01:58.280 --> 00:02:00.560
over that region
that we care about.

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:03.760
This is the domain of our
parameters, this region R.

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:09.163
And this is how we've
manipulated any of the surface

00:02:09.163 --> 00:02:10.830
integrals that we've
come across so far.

00:02:10.830 --> 00:02:13.430
We've turned them
into double integrals

00:02:13.430 --> 00:02:15.440
over the domain
of the parameters.

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:19.240
So this is going to turn into a
double integral over the domain

00:02:19.240 --> 00:02:21.720
of our parameters, which is
the region R. It's the region

00:02:21.720 --> 00:02:25.120
R in the xy plane right up here.

